result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) and Operating w/ PAC (2nd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (2nd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Christian C. Killian was found guilty of OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Christian C. Killian in court with attorney Kyle Robert Reimann.  Larry Eugene Nelson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State recites joint recommendation:  Cts 2-4: dismissed.  Ct 1: amended to OWI 3rd.  45 days jail, consecutive to 15CT132, w/ Huber; $1744.00; $40.50; 24 mo DLR, cc to 15CT132; 24 mo IID, cc to 15CT132; AODA & dsp; DNA submission.    Court verbally reviews charges/penalties with the defendant.  NC plea given and entered.   Defendant sworn by the Clerk.    Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights form - colloquy given.  Defendant freely, willingly, knowledgeably and intelligently enters into the plea agreement and joint recommendation.  Court accepts the joint recommendation and sentences the defendant accordingly.
Plea/sentencing hearing on March 19, 2018 at 02:00 pm.

Defendant Christian C. Killian in court with attorney Kyle Robert Reimann.  Larry Eugene Nelson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court hears Mr. Reimann - defendant was ready to go today, but now requests an adjournment to 4/18/2018, as defendant has many health issues, and he wishes adjourn the plea/sentencing in order to take care of these issues before going to jail.  Def continues regular ATTIC testing, and although he has his AODA assessment on 2/21/2018, there is a follow up on 3/22/2018.  Court hears LEN - def has had medical issues, but he opposes another continuance and gives reasons.  Court recounts the case history, reluctant to set this off again.  Reimann again addresses the court.  LEN does not want something catastrophic to happen in the interim in the event of a relapse.  Nelson wants to go to sentencing.  Reimann requests continuance - states his client is not ready to proceed today.  Court continues matter to matter tp 3-19-2018 at 3:00.  Discussion held on getting information from doctor on the immediacy of surgery.  3/19/2018 at 2:00 pm is now set.  If we do not got to plea/sentencing on that date, it is required that something is needed from doctor.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for March 19, 2018 at 02:00 pm.
